{"category"=>"Benefit Resources", "name"=>"Home Energy Assistance Program (HEAP)", "phone"=>" 800-692-0557 for after-hours heating emergency assistance. ", "address"=>"", "website"=>"", "contact"=>"", "referral"=>"Fill out an application (here) or you can direct clients to an advocate to help.", "eligibility"=>"Refer clients to Elena, Rosie, or Christina - they can help clients with eligibility, documentation, and applications.", "insurance"=>"", "notes"=>"Regular Benefits: The application provides $21 - $575+ to households based on income, heating source, and housing type. Clients can also access one-time emergency resources.Equipment Repair/Replacement available.\r\nCLIENTS WHO RECEIVE HEAP CAN RECEIVE UP TO $500 MORE IN FOOD STAMPS, regardless of HEAP amounts! Even if clients are ineligible, we can point them to other utility resources. \r\nClients can also access one-time emergency resources IF (1) their heat is shut off or scheduled to be shut off, (2) they meet the income guidelines or receive SNAP/TANF, and (3) their available resources are under $2,000 (or under $3,000 if a household member is over 60). Equipment Repair/Replacement: Applications must be made in person at the local Job Center. Clients can receive up to $6,500 to maintain the operations of their heating system.", "created_at"=>DateTime.parse('Wed, 07 Jan 2015 17:15:28 UTC +00:00'), "updated_at"=> DateTime.parse('Mon, 02 Feb 2015 20:23:13 UTC +00:00')},
